## Part 0: Shared Infrastructure

### 0A. Onboarding State Manager (localStorage-based)

All onboarding components share a single source of truth. A custom hook and a lightweight context will manage onboarding state without touching the database.

**New file:** `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\hooks\useOnboardingState.js`

This hook manages:
- `onboarding_welcome_completed` (boolean) -- has the user finished or skipped the welcome flow
- `onboarding_tips_dismissed` (Set of string tip IDs) -- which tooltips have been seen
- `onboarding_tips_global_off` (boolean) -- user chose "don't show tips"
- `onboarding_checklist_dismissed` (boolean) -- user dismissed the checklist widget
- `onboarding_checklist_items` (object) -- tracks completion: `{profile: true, firstPost: false, followWriter: false, exploreTrending: false, saveBookmark: false}`

The hook structure:
```js
