}
.checklist-item--done {
  opacity: 0.5;
  cursor: default;
}
.checklist-item--done:hover {
  opacity: 0.5;
}

.checklist-checkbox {
  width: 20px;
  height: 20px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  border: 2px solid var(--border-light);
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  transition: border-color 0.2s, background 0.2s;
}
.checklist-checkbox--checked {
  border-color: var(--accent-sage);
  background: var(--accent-sage);
}

.checklist-item-label {
  font-family: "Outfit", sans-serif;
  font-size: 0.85rem;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  flex: 1;
}
.checklist-item--done .checklist-item-label {
  text-decoration: line-through;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

.checklist-item-arrow {
  color: var(--text-muted);
  font-size: 1.1rem;
}

.checklist-dismiss-btn,
.checklist-collapse-btn {
  background: none;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  padding: 4px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  transition: color 0.15s;
}
.checklist-dismiss-btn:hover,
.checklist-collapse-btn:hover {
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}

@media (max-width: 480px) {
  .onboarding-checklist {
    border-left-width: 2px;
    border-radius: 12px;
  }
}
```

### Auto-Completion Detection

The onboarding context hook watches user data to auto-mark checklist items:

```js
// Inside useOnboardingState or a separate useOnboardingAutoTrack hook:

// Profile: marked complete when user has name + bio + image_url
useEffect(() => {
  if (userData?.name && userData?.bio && userData?.image_url) {
    updateChecklist('profile', true);
  }
}, [userData]);

// First post: listen for successful journal creation
// This can be triggered from the Editor's onSubmit success callback
// Or check journal count from existing queries

// Follow writer: triggered from the follow mutation success
// Explore trending: triggered when user visits /home/explore
// Save bookmark: triggered from bookmark mutation success
```

**Implementation approach for auto-tracking:**

Since some actions (follow, bookmark) already use React Query mutations in `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\utils\useMutation.js`, the cleanest approach is to add an `onSuccess` callback in those hooks that checks and updates onboarding state.

For page visits (explore), use a `useEffect` in `PostCards.jsx` that detects when `location.pathname === '/home/explore'` and marks `exploreTrending: true`.

### Integration into Home Feed

In `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\HomePage\postCards\PostCards.jsx`, insert the `OnboardingChecklist` component right before the `DashboardBriefing`:

```jsx
{!isSearchMode && session && !isFollowingFeed && (
  <OnboardingChecklist
    onOpenEditor={() => handleOpenTextEditor()}
    onNavigate={(path) => navigate(path)}
  />
)}
{!isSearchMode && session && (
  <DashboardBriefing onWriteResponse={...} />
)}
```

This positions the checklist at the very top of the feed, above the dashboard briefing, giving new users immediate visibility.

